cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for improving the accuracy of prepositional phrase attachment models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of embeddings and learning algorithms, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses semantic concepts and WordNet, which are related to artificial intelligence and knowledge representation, making cs.AI a possible category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for estimating the distribution over relevant semantic concepts, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
